                                   Revisions

The following modifications have been made:

Version 1.3:
Levels: I've redone Level 1 of Episode Five and Level 8 of Episode Six.  A
*very* minor bug with pre-saved game #8 is fixed.
Miscellaneous: Compiled .BAT files into .COM files with a utility called
BAT2EXEC.EXE by Doug Boling.

Version 1.2:
Levels: One level of Episode Five had a bug.  This problem was located in a
secret area.  A door and an extra Floor Code were all that was needed to fix
the problem.  The only change the player will notice is an additional door.
Also note that Level Nine of Episode Six is partly redone.  The level's new
formula is to build up the suspense.
Graphics: I remade the graphics of the steel plating (again), the red bricks
(they're slightly bigger now, with a little more texture), the unlocked doors,
and the door sides.  I made minor changes to other graphics I made.
Miscellaneous: The wording of the documentation is somewhat more compact.
Flawed reference to Episode Four is now corrected to Episode Five (in the Bugs
section).  The game's new story has been altered slightly, though the plot is
exactly the same.  The Bugs section has more information on the author's
future plans.  The documentation has a quick-reference section added for those
who don't want to read the lengthy documentation.

Version 1.1:
Graphics: In this version, the texture of the Silver Stone Walls is improved.
I originally made a graphical mistake with one or more of these walls, but the
mistake was in one of the places I added texture, so the problem was fixed
automatically.  I made minor changes to a few other wall images.

    If I release future versions, I'll probably make more new graphics and
redo one or more levels.  I plan to replace the grey brick walls, the red
bricks, the brown canyon walls, and the blue panelling.  Expect things like
Brown Bricks, Diamond tiles, and so on.
