                                     Bugs

     I have thoroughly beta-tested each and every one of these new levels on
the highest difficulty.  None of them have given me any bugs - not even "Out
of memory!" errors.
     The only problems occur in the original levels as well.  They are
problems in the game itself - the EXE files.  Some of these bugs are:  Dogs
sometimes disappearing when stopping in a doorway to bite you, two sides of a
particular block sometimes changing into a darkened Gray Stone wall (after
loading a saved game before starting a new game), Flashing Screen Borders
(elaborated in MapEdit's documentation), and a technical Moving Actors problem
(the last bug also exists with the Pac-man ghosts and the sprite of B.J.
running at the end of Episodes One and Five).
     When I learn the language "C" better, I plan to dig into the source code
and fix these bugs myself.  The "Out of Memory!" errors and flashing screen
borders will be very easy to fix;  the problem can be fixed manually by the
player without modification to the program, but I'd rather have the game fix
the problem automatically - don't you?
     The new EXE file MIGHT have the menus use two digitized sounds -
including a new sound I'd record myself.  I also plan to have the game support
more IRQ settings.  I would also like to add six extra door images;  the doors
would change to an unlatched image when they are moving and "latch back" to
their original image when they've completely closed.  I think that would be a
nice effect.
