                                     Story

     You come home from what you thought was a successful mission and plan
many days with your movie-star wife.  However, the General calls you a day
later with bad news: Neither Schabbs nor Hitler were killed - you annihilated
simple clones.  After hearing this news, you are NOT happy.
     Though your actions DID stop Operation Eisenfaust, an even more
horrendous plot is underway to release clones all across the world, starting
with the U.S..  The clones will cause such confusion that the world will
become too vulnerable to Germany, and Hitler will conquer.
     America's best spy learns that only Schabbs and Hitler know particular
Top Secret information involving these clones.  Without that information, the
plan can never be carried out.  You are ordered to go back and destroy Schabbs
and Hitler.
     You reach the entrance of Dr. Schabbs's castle and look all around you,
but not above you.  Seconds later, you're tackled, and you awaken in a
dungeon, miles away from where you want to be.
     You wittingly break the neck of a Nazi guard and snatch his gun, only
THIS TIME someone heard you.  You start to hear footsteps, and you're ready
for action (you hope).  Assuming you survive the dungeon threat, you
contemplate your duty ahead, and the odds against you.
     One man.  Thousands of enemies.  Halls ahead that are purposely built to
confuse the escapees.  Greater threats against you than ever before.  Fail,
and the U.S. goes to Hitler.  Win, and ... well ... the U.S. goes to Clinton
in 1992.
     Man, it just doesn't pay to get up in the morning.
